race.comment: QUADRA (10) went forward and gave a great sight before finishing third last time out over 1609m at Colonial Downs (Turf). Beautifully placed and is sure to take plenty of stopping. YOU'RE THE ONE (5) is in fine form and hasn't missed the frame in her past six starts. Last time out she finished third over 1207m at this track. Winning claims yet again. BIG DREAMER (2) is a genuine four-year-old filly who resumed with a solid second last time out at this track (Dirt) over 1207m. Among the leading chances. MIZOULA (12) has put together back-to-back placings, the latest when 2 lengths away in second over 1106m at Colonial Downs (Turf). Likely to be about the money again. Something for the Multiples: DARK DUTCHESS (8)
